-- Merkel Meets Sarkozy; New Hampshire Votes: Week Ahead Jan. 9-13
-- B y   G r e g   M i l e s ,   D i c k   S c h u m a c h e r   a n d   K e a t   K i a n   K o h
-- 2012-01-09T05:00:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/merkel-meets-sarkozy-new-hampshire-votes-week-ahead-jan-9-13.html
German Chancellor  Angela Merkel  and
French President Nicolas Sarkozy try again to quell the euro-
region’s debt crisis by developing plans for increased fiscal
coordination among member states. European Central Bank
President Mario Draghi will speak to journalists after a board
meeting that likely will leave the ECB’s key rate at 1 percent.  Mitt Romney probably will win the New Hampshire Republican
presidential primary, adding to his momentum for the party’s
nomination. Companies unveil products at the  Consumer
Electronics Show  in Las Vegas, while carmakers showcase new
models at the Detroit Auto Show. Alcoa Inc. will kick off the
U.S. fourth-quarter earnings season.  Chinese inflation may have slowed in December, which will
feed the debate on whether the nation’s economy is headed for a
so-called soft landing. The  Federal Reserve ’s report on regional
economic condition, or Beige Book, will offer clues about
whether the U.S. recovery is gathering steam.  MONDAY, Jan. 9  To contact the reporters on this story:
